organic_results.title: Women's Labor Force Participation and Preschool Enrollment: A Cross-National Perspective, 1965-80
organic_results.snippet: This article describes the worldwide expansion of preschool enrollments between 1965 and 1980 and summarizes the findings of a longitudinal study linking expanded preschool enrollments with women's increased levels of participation in the labor force. Economic, political, and organizational explanations for the expansion of preschool enrollment were also tested in the study.
